<P>TO THE LINNAEAN SOCIETY, THE FOLLOWING FRAGMENTS (WHICH ARE INTENDED TO ILLUSTRATE, IN SOME DEGREE, THE NATURAL HISTORY OF A COUNTRY EXTREMELY INTERESTING TO PHILOSOPHERS, AND HITHERTO VERY IMPERFECTLY EXPLORED) ARE, WITH GREAT RESPECT, INSCRIBED BY THE SOCIETY'S FRIEND AND BROTHER-MEMBER, BENJAMIN SMITH BARTON.</P>
