<CELL>Calandra-Lark. (May-Bird, Gra&s;s-Bird.)</CELL>
<CELL>Andromeda aborea (Sorrel-Tree), Fagus ameri|cana (Che&s;nut), Juglans nigra (Black Walnut), Juglans cinerea (Butternut), Aralia nudicaulis (Sar&s;aparilla), Berberi, vulgaris, Platanus oc|cidentalis (Button-Tree, Sycamore), Crataegus Crus galli, Pi&s;um &s;ativum, Veratrum luteum, Salvia lyrata, and many other vegetables, in flower.</CELL>
<CELL>&nbsp;</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>Motacilla vermivora. (G.)</CELL>
<CELL>Worm-Eater.</CELL>
<CELL>&nbsp;</CELL>
<CELL>A &s;pecies of Curculio (Fruit-devouring Weavel) is now bu&s;y, at night-time, in darting and de|po&s;iting its eggs in the young fruit of Plumbs, Cherries, Peaches, Apples, Pears, Me&s;pilus, Juglans, &amp;c.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>&mdash;28.</CELL>
<CELL>Certhia floridana (mihi).</CELL>
<CELL>Great Yellow-throated-Wren of Florida.</CELL>
